s"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7 40a Abs 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Asparagus The profit from asparagus cultivation is to be determined by comparing the operating income actually achieved and the operating expenses, provided this can be proven on the basis of records"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "If no records are kept and proof is therefore not possible, the following guidelines can be applied per hectare of yield area: 1983/841984/851985/861986/87 (1984 harvest) (1985 harvest) (1986 harvest) (1987 harvest) DMDMDMDM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Revenues27500331002950024200 Real development costs8300820080008000 Profit from asparagus growing19200249002150016200 The average profit is to be applied from the 4th year of cultivation of the asparagus area, whereby the first year is the planting year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Direct sales and the producers' own consumption are taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Proportional wage expenses for permanent workers as well as temporary wages can also be deducted if they are proven or substantiated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "It must be checked whether this has also led to wage tax consequences"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The tax offices are not bound by the above guideline rates if these lead to an incorrect profit estimate in individual cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "When determining the profit, the VAT amounts received are to be counted as operating income, and the input tax amounts paid as operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The sales tax and the input taxes are in the o"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Alignment rate already included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "bb) Viticulture 1 Profits of the 1981/82 financial year (1981 harvest) and the following financial years a) General The profits of wine-growing operations not required to keep accounts are to be determined according to Section 4 (3) EStG based on the excess of operating income over operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "For the declaration of the information required for this, the taxpayers are to be requested to submit the \"Annex ESt 2 Wine\" with the income tax return"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "If the information provided by the taxpayers is incomplete or gives cause for doubt, the stated operating income can be checked in individual cases on the basis of the proof of delivery, payment receipts and statements of cooperatives"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Such tests can also be carried out on a random basis in other individual cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "If the tax office after the final income tax assessment or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Profit determination determines that the taxpayer has achieved higher operating income, the tax and assessment notices must always be changed if the new facts take effect"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "b) Failure to submit the ESt 2 wine annex If the taxpayer does not comply with his tax declaration obligations, it is up to the tax office to decide which tax law measures are to be taken"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Consider z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Compulsory measures according to \u00a7\u00a7 328 to 335 AO, profit estimation according to \u00a7 162 AO, late surcharges according to \u00a7 152 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 93 AO, information from cooperatives and producer groups can also be obtained in individual cases when determining the basis for estimates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "c) Operating expenses The actual construction costs are to be taken into account with the following lump sum for building costs if the taxpayer does not provide evidence or credible evidence of the operating expenses in total by means of records or receipts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "1981/821982/831983/841984/851985/861986 / 87DM / haDM / haDM / haDM / haDM / haDM / ha745076007600760077007700"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The annual expenses for fertilization, pest control, maintenance, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "that are incurred in the period up to the full yield of the vines cannot be deducted separately, as these expenses are part of the production costs of the vineyards and are included as depreciation in the building costs flat rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "A vineyard is only completed and therefore depreciable when it is fully operational"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "This is the case for the first time in the 3 year, whereby the year of planting counts as 1 year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The lump sum cannot be deducted for an earlier financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The assessment basis for the depreciation, which is taken into account in the flat rate for building costs, also includes the maintenance costs up to the completion of the vineyard"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer does not provide evidence of his actual operating expenses and he makes use of the lump sum for building costs, it is to be assumed that he has exercised his right of valuation according to no.321 of the BMF letter of 15 December 1981 (BStBl I 1981 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "878; Landw- Kartei F IV 2 a) has taken advantage of the activation of the maintenance costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, the maintenance costs have been deducted as operating expenses during the production phase of the vineyard, the flat-rate building costs must be reduced accordingly, because it includes the depreciation for the maintenance costs that are part of the production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The lump sum for building costs cannot be set in full even for leased businesses and for leased individual plots if the lessor is the owner of the vineyard and therefore only he is entitled to the depreciation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, there are no concerns about not reducing the flat-rate building costs for smaller plot areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In the case of the free transfer of use, on the other hand, a reduction is not possible because the right of use with regard to the transferred assets must take into account an annual contribution to the amount of the depreciation amounts from the beneficiary (BFH, ruling"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "2 8 1983 BStBl 1983 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "735 739 m"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the tax authorities are not bound by the flat rate for building costs if it can be assumed that taking it into account will lead to an incorrect profit estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the lump sum, the following documented expenses can also be deducted: Contribution payments for hail insurance, expenses for frost protection (a lump sum for this is no longer to be taken into account since the 1975/76 financial year), land consolidation costs attributable to viticulture (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Expenses for the new construction of the road and water network including wall construction), debt and lease interest insofar as they are attributable to viticulture, VAT amounts actually paid to the tax office, wages for excl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Workers employed in viticulture (if paid workers were employed in both agriculture and viticulture, then the wage share can only be taken into account insofar as it relates to work in viticulture"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "When considering wages, it is important to ensure that the wage tax consequences, possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7 40a Abs 2 EStG), expenses for soil disinfection (the expenses can be evenly distributed on request for 2 to 5 years), expenses for the removal of storm damage on embankments and vineyards minus public subsidies; self-borne expenses can be spread over 2 to 5 financial years on request (decree FinMin BW of 10 1 1984 S-1916 - 3/83)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Depreciation of the production costs of retaining walls on steep slopes (normal useful life: concrete construction 50 years, stones 20 years), costs of irrigation systems (normal useful life: mobile 8 years, stationary 10 years), expenses for bird repellant nets, wild fences, for pest control with helicopters to compensate for the factual Additional costs per helicopter spraying, if the number of helicopter sprayings and the area flown over can be proven"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Because of the costs of restoring vineyards that have been damaged by natural events, see L II 1 1981/821982/831983/841984/851985/861986 / 87DM / haDM / haDM / haDM / haDM / haDM / ha160160160160160160 self-expanding companies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The costs for expansion, bottle filling and equipment as well as for distribution can also be taken into account with the following lump sums per liter of wine produced as follows: For expansion costs 025 DM for bottles (including labels and corks) 050 DM for sales 025 DM2 External audits When external audits are carried out also to pay attention to the determination of operating income, which may have been concealed by the fact that harvest quantities are delivered to cooperatives and producer groups under the names of family members and other persons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Businesses that develop themselves as well as businesses that sell their wine in their own broom bar must comply with the Wine Act (last amended by the version of 27 August 1982 Federal Law Gazette I 1982 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "1196) keep cellar books (\"autumn books\") in which the entry and exit of the wines as well as the alcohol content and the harvest quantity are to be entered in relation to the district, location and grape variety (regulation of the state government of 20 September 1982)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The wine-growing companies have to fulfill these recording obligations also for tax purposes (\u00a7 140 AO, AO-Kartei \u00a7 140 card 1 no 66)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the wine stocks and the storage room (barrel and tank room) are to be reported on certain key dates (\u00a7 4 Wine Industry Act, Federal Law Gazette I 1977 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "453)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "These records and reports are to be used when checking the operating income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "cc) Horticultural use Vegetable, flower and ornamental plant cultivation The following list of the framework rates for determining the sales and profits of horticultural companies serves as an aid for checking the declared sales and profits and can also be used for estimates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The framework rates listed in Section A of the Annex are gross revenues from self-made horticultural products, which are calculated per ar on the basis of wholesale prices incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "VAT (gross wholesale prices) have been achieved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "As far as the corresponding production conditions are known in flower and ornamental plant cultivation, in case groups 6 to 8 of the list up to and including 1984, the revenues should be taken from the upper half of the frame in the case of predominantly potted plants and the lower half of the frame in the case of predominantly cut flowers; from 1985 onwards, with predominantly potted plants, the rates should be around 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "increased and with predominantly cut flower cultivation by 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "be decreased"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In the case of deliveries to end consumers, the proceeds from the predominant sale of vegetables are 40 to 70 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "and with the predominant sale of ornamental plants by 50 to 90 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "to increase"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "When selling at weekly markets, the lower half of the frame should be used as the basis, and when selling in your own shop, the upper half of the frame"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The sales from deliveries of purchased items (third-party products) as well as the fees from other services (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Gardening and landscaping, grave maintenance) must be determined in particular"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In the case of commercial (non-agricultural) nurseries and agricultural nurseries that have opted for standard taxation in accordance with Section 24 (4) UStG, the gross revenues for VAT purposes determined on the basis of the framework rates must be adjusted for the VAT contained therein"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "However, the net profit must be calculated from the (unreduced) gross revenue"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "When determining profits, external wages are only to be taken into account if they are proven or at least made credible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In addition, it must be ensured that wage tax consequences are drawn from this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Debt and lea