 "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In addition, asserted increased deductions, special depreciations and profit deductions - as far as permitted - must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "From 1985 the profit rate for flower and ornamental plant cultivation with predominantly pot plant cultivation is around 10 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "to be reduced and with predominantly cut flower growing by 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "to increase"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Fruit growing operating income The actual operating income that the taxpayer has to state in Appendix L and in the \"Appendix VAT / ESt for gardeners\" must be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Operating income includes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "also the compensation from the hail insurance as well as aid for the hail insurance premiums"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In order to check the declared farm income and to record the farmers, the ALS provides the tax offices with empirical values \u200b\u200bon average income per hectare of intensive fruit growing area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Operating expenses If the material costs cannot be proven in total by records or receipts, they can be taken into account by the following building costs flat rate per hectare of yield area: 1983/841984/851985/861986 / 87DMDMDMDMKernobst5900 1) 6100 1) 6200 1) 6200 1) Stone fruit4900 1) 5000 1) 5100 1) 5100 1) Bushberries (without raspberries and blackberries) 4700 1) 4800 1) 4900 1) 4900 1) Raspberries, blackberries 6300 1) 6400 1) 6500 1) 6500 1) Strawberries for self-pickers 8900900091009100 Strawberries fresh market goods9300 1) 9400 1) 9500 1) 9500 1) +) Proven expenses for packaging material and in-house storage and cooling facilities can be deducted in addition to the flat-rate building costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The proportionate wages, debt interest and contributions to hail insurance are each separately outside the specified profit target rate or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Building costs flat rate to be taken into account when determining the profit if they are proven"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "It is important to ensure that the wage tax conclusions are drawn"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The tax offices are not bound to these flat-rate building costs if their consideration in individual cases leads to an incorrect profit estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "If the maintenance costs have been deducted as operating expenses during the production phase of the orchard, the lump sums for building costs must be reduced accordingly (see No. 1b)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "In this sense, only the plants with full yield including individual young trees in between belong to the yield area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Closed rows of young plants, even within an existing system, do not belong to the yield area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "For pome and stone fruit, bush berries and raspberries, it can be assumed that on a farm with the same fruit-growing area, approx"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "There are new, closed systems in the area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The following values \u200b\u200bcan be used as a basis for the question of when the orchard is in full yield and with regard to the useful life and the depreciation rate according to Section 7 (1) EStG: fruit type production period minimum useful life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "ApplesPlanting year + 4 years10 years10PearsPlanting year + 4 years15 years7Sour cherriesPlanting year + 4 years12 years8Sweet cherriesPlanting year + 7 years20 years5PeachesPlanting year + 4 years10 years10Plus planting year + 7 years20 years can with 50 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "the gross income incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Sales tax will be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The nurseries also include nurseries and nursery gardens"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The ALS can be used to determine the operating income and profits as well as for the taxation of the operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "dd) Distilleries a) Cap distilleries Cap distilleries have official documents on the amount produced and the income which can be viewed by the taxpayer in individual cases or requested from him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The profit can be as high as 27 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "of revenues including sales tax are estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Proportional wages and debt interest must be deducted separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Profits from the sale of a distilling right are to be recorded in accordance with Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "b) Severance payment distilleries The tax offices are sent control notifications after the end of each burning year about the quantities of fuel produced, the sales and profits determined on the basis of standard rates and the sales tax attributable to the sales"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "Proportional wage expenses and debt interest are to be deducted in particular if they are proven or credible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The remuneration for the burning of fabric owners must be added to the operating income for VAT purposes shown in the control notifications"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "If no information is given about the remuneration, a boiler volume of 120 to 150 l can be set at DM 30 per output"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "The resulting profit can be increased to 45 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "to be appreciated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "If a substantial amount of remuneration has been received from the distillery for fabric owners, it must be checked whether the distillery is to be treated as a commercial enterprise (cf. A VI 1 page 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0079134.xml"}, "text": "--- Income tax / wage tax / church tax Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg agriculture"}]